  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nIn Nethermind.service, the line `ProtectSystem=strict` prohibits the application from reading other volumes. This effectively prevents you from putting your database dir on another volume.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n- Create a datadir on another volume\r\n- Point to this datadir in your Nethermind.service file\r\n- Try to run Nethermind. It stops with \"IO error - Read-only file system\"\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nIt should be possible to put datadir on other volume.\r\n\r\n**Solution**\r\nRemove line `ProtectSystem=strict`\r\n",
